---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Gene Community"
	description="Connect with the Gene programming language community, contribute to the runtime, and stay informed."
>
	<header class="page-header">
		<h1>Community</h1>
		<p>
			Gene grows through open collaboration. Join discussions about AI-first language design, share feedback on homoiconic features, and help shape the roadmap through spec-driven development.
		</p>
	</header>

	<section class="grid">
		<article class="card">
			<h2>GitHub</h2>
			<p>
				Track development, open issues, and submit pull requests. The runtime, compiler, and website all live in the
				public repository.
			</p>
                        <a class="button-link" href="https://github.com/gene-lang/gene" rel="noopener">github.com/gene-lang/gene →</a>
		</article>

		<article class="card">
			<h2>OpenSpec proposals</h2>
			<p>
				Larger changes start with an OpenSpec proposal. Read existing specs, or draft a new one to propose language,
				tooling, or documentation improvements.
			</p>
                        <a class="button-link" href="https://github.com/gene-lang/gene/tree/main/openspec" rel="noopener">
				OpenSpec workflow →
			</a>
		</article>

		<article class="card">
			<h2>Chat &amp; support</h2>
			<p>
				Join the community channel (Discord/Matrix planned) to ask questions, pair on debugging, or discuss Gene&apos;s roadmap.
			</p>
			<span class="coming-soon">Community chat launching soon</span>
		</article>

		<article class="card">
			<h2>Showcase</h2>
			<p>
				Share projects built with Gene. We feature libraries, production use cases, and experiments from the community.
			</p>
			<a class="button-link" href="https://github.com/gene-lang/gene/discussions" rel="noopener">Submit a project →</a>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section class="newsletter">
		<h2>Stay in the loop</h2>
		<p>
			A lightweight newsletter and RSS feed will launch with the first public release. Until then, watch the GitHub
			repository for updates.
		</p>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.page-header {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	.page-header h1 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 3vw, 2.7rem);
	}

	.page-header p {
		color: var(--color-muted);
		max-width: 44rem;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.grid {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
	}

	.card {
		background: var(--color-surface);
		border-radius: 1.1rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		padding: 1.7rem;
		box-shadow: 0 18px 32px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.75rem;
	}

	.card h2 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 1.4rem;
	}

	.card p {
		margin: 0;
		color: var(--color-muted);
	}

	.button-link {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.35rem;
		color: var(--color-accent);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.coming-soon {
		color: var(--color-muted);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-style: italic;
	}

	.newsletter {
		margin-top: 4rem;
		background: var(--color-surface);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		border-radius: 1.1rem;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		box-shadow: 0 16px 28px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		max-width: 40rem;
	}

	.newsletter h2 {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.newsletter p {
		margin: 0;
		color: var(--color-muted);
	}
</style>
